node.text:
Today I want to share with all of you unusual story, that started few weeks ago. I was contacted by @borillazzz and @pikabu with idea to make art collaboration and rise awareness about amazing animal shelter @klyaksa_dom , where traumatised cats and cats with special needs live. People from @klyaksa_dom took some photos of their wonderful inhabitants, sent them to me and I made a few drawings. One of the drawings was picked and transformed into a huge street art project on the wall (biggest @dailypurrr drawing till this day) which was created with help of cool people from @Stenograffia. Main character of this drawing is true hero, cat named Larry, who survived car accident, fought for his life, but now he's fully recovered, thanks to people from @klyaksa_dom and is in search of a new home as well as other his friends from this animal shelter. All this amazing idea and performance took a place in Ekaterinburg, Russia. I hope you will like this story and will pay attention to this animal shelter. Who knows, maybe one day you will find a good friend for yourself among cats with special needs and make their life happy again.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
What was your most important, meaningful surprise/gift you ever received? My parents never had a lot of money, but one time they saved up some money and bought me Playstation 1. I don't remember, It was my birthday or they just wanted to make me happy. Still remember how I went home after soccer match and found out that PS 1 standing in front of TV with FIFA disc. I was so damn happy that day! ❤️
.
